# [[ markdown(project_name) ]]

[[ markdown(project_purpose) ]]

This repository uses the dstack documentation-first, Beads-backed development workflow.

## Getting started

Install the workflow skills:

```bash
npx --yes skills@1.5.16 add RobertDeRose/dstack
```

The setup workflow already validates the scaffold and initializes Beads when `bd` is available. Start a session with:

```bash
bd prime
bd ready --type epic --label workflow:feature --json --limit 0
```

If setup reported Beads as outstanding, initialize it once with `bd init --stealth --skip-agents`, then rerun the commands
above.

Use the installed lifecycle skills:

```text
/plan-features
/start-feature <number>-<slug>
/implement-feature <number>-<slug>
/close-feature <number>-<slug>
/audit-project
```

Validate or serve the documentation:

```bash
uv run scripts/check-docs.py
mdbook serve docs --open
```

The project was generated from `RobertDeRose/dstack` with Copier. Commit the scaffold before applying future template updates with `/update-project` or `copier update --defaults`.
